
### 2. `.gitignore`

The `.gitignore` file is used to specify files and directories that Git should ignore.

```plaintext
# Binaries for programs and plugins
..exe
*.dll
*.so
*.dylib

# Go workspace
bin/
pkg/

# Logs
*.log

# OS-generated files
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Go modules
vendor/

# Environment variables
.env

# IDE/editor config files
.idea/
.vscode/

# http or db files
*.http
*.db